sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Platform Operator
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as ModelRegistry Controller
    participant CatalogCtrl as ModelCatalog Controller
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant RouteAPI as OpenShift Route API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant AuthCR as Auth CR<br/>(platform API)
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KubeRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RestAPI as Model Registry REST API<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,RouteAPI: Flow 1: ModelRegistry Instance Provisioning

    User->>K8sAPI: Create ModelRegistry CR<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate (mutating)<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated CR (defaults, OAuth→kube-rbac-proxy migration)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate (validating)<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation result
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR created

    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: ModelRegistry CR
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment (REST API + kube-rbac-proxy)<br/>SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service, NetworkPolicy, RBAC<br/>SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create PostgreSQL Deployment + Secret<br/>SA Token (if auto-provision)
    Controller->>RouteAPI: Create Routes (HTTP edge + HTTPS reencrypt)<br/>SA Token

    Note over Client,RestAPI: Flow 2: Model Registry REST API Access

    Client->>Router: HTTPS request<br/>TLS (edge/reencrypt), Bearer Token
    Router->>KubeRBAC: Forward to sidecar<br/>HTTPS 8443, TLS (serving cert)
    KubeRBAC->>K8sAPI: TokenReview<br/>HTTPS 443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>KubeRBAC: Token valid
    KubeRBAC->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS 443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>KubeRBAC: Access granted
    KubeRBAC->>RestAPI: Proxied request<br/>HTTP 8080 (localhost)
    RestAPI->>PostgreSQL: Query metadata<br/>5432/TCP, Password, SSLMode configurable
    PostgreSQL-->>RestAPI: Results
    RestAPI-->>KubeRBAC: Response
    KubeRBAC-->>Router: HTTPS response
    Router-->>Client: HTTPS response

    Note over CatalogCtrl,AuthCR: Flow 3: Model Catalog Provisioning

    CatalogCtrl->>K8sAPI: Watch: Auth CR, ConfigMaps, platform ModelRegistry CR
    K8sAPI-->>CatalogCtrl: Resource events
    CatalogCtrl->>AuthCR: GET admin groups<br/>SA Token
    AuthCR-->>CatalogCtrl: Admin group list
    CatalogCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create/update Catalog Deployment, PostgreSQL, RBAC<br/>SA Token
    CatalogCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create admin Role/RoleBinding (if groups configured)<br/>SA Token
    CatalogCtrl->>RouteAPI: Create model-catalog-https Route<br/>SA Token
